28/02/2006
MOSCOW, Russia -- Turkey and Russia began a two-day joint military drill on Tuesday (28 February). It is taking place in the southwest part of the Black Sea. 
In other news, Iraqi Prime Minister Ibrahim al-Jaafari is visiting Ankara. Turkish counterpart Recep Tayyip Erdogan has said the focus would be the rising sectarian violence in neighbouring Iraq. (Itar-Tass, TurkishPress.com - 27/02/06) 
